/nWe twa hae run about the braes, 
And pou'd the gowans fine; 
But we've wander'd mony a weary fit, 
Sin' auld lang syne.
/nFor auld lang syne, my jo, 
for auld lang syne, 
We'll tak' a cup o' kindness yet, 
For auld lang syne.
/nWe twa hae paidl'd in the burn, 
Frae morning sun till dine; 
But seas between us braid hae roar'd 
Sin' auld lang syne.
/nFor auld lang syne, my jo, 
for auld lang syne, 
We'll tak' a cup o' kindness yet, 
For auld lang syne.
/nAnd there's a hand, my trusty fiere! 
And gie's a hand o' thine! 
And we'll tak' a right gude-willie waught, 
For auld lang syne.
/nFor auld lang syne, my jo, 
for auld lang syne, 
We'll tak' a cup o' kindness yet, 
For auld lang syne.
